      "blocks": {
        "rich_text_iA6zry": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Heading",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>What are the different types of Diamonds?</h1>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "follow_us_WqTh9e": {
          "type": "follow_us",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Follow Us on"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_kMfyzk": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Shopping for a diamond can feel like stepping into a world full of sparkle, tradition, and a lot of jargon. Whether it’s for an <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lab Grown Diamond Engagement Ring\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Engagement Ring</span></a>, a gift, or a personal treat, knowing what type of diamond you’re buying makes a big difference. And here’s the good news: once you understand the basics, it's a lot less intimidating than it seems.</p><p>We’re not just talking about size or sparkle here. There are real differences between the kinds of diamonds available today, from how they're formed to how they're priced and how they impact the world. </p><p>So if you're wondering whether to go for the classic diamond or something a little more colourful, this guide will help you feel much more confident.</p><p>Let’s break it all down.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_BpVw9t": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Lab Grown Diamonds: The New-Gen Sparkle",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>Lab Grown Diamonds: The New-Gen Sparkle</h1>",
            "custom_id": "lab"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_gTCBWR": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Single_Diamond_Image_1080_700.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Unlike Mined Diamonds that naturally occur deep underground, Lab Grown Diamonds are carefully crafted in Labs. Scientists replicate the formation of Natural Diamonds using advanced technology to create diamonds that cause no harm to the environment.</p><p>Lab Grown Diamonds have the same chemical make up as Mined Diamonds, shine just as beautifully and are just as tough. With no physical differences, lab grown diamonds can only be told apart from natural diamonds through specialist equipment.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bYjbXk": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The only difference is that they come without the damage to our planet and are ethically more conscious. Since Lab Grown Diamonds do not require large mining operations, they also cost much less than Mined Diamonds. </p><p>If you’re someone who likes modern solutions and clean sourcing, these could be exactly what you're looking for.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Q3hQcb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Colored Diamonds: Sparkle with a Twist",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Colored Diamonds: Sparkle with a Twist</h2>",
            "custom_id": "colored"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_jph8xc": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Colored_Diamond_1080_600.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Not into the classic white or clear diamond look? You’re not alone. Diamonds also come in beautiful shades, soft yellows, deep blues, and even pinks. Naturally colored ones can be rare and prized, which often pushes up the cost.</p><p>Lab Created Colored Diamonds are now becoming more popular, offering similar looks with less of a hit to your wallet. If you're drawn to something playful, bold, or completely unique, these colorful options are definitely worth exploring.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_anmPcL": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Mined Diamonds: The Old-School Sparkle",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Mined Diamonds: The Old-School Sparkle</h2>",
            "custom_id": "mined"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_Xw37jX": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Miners_1080_600.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Mined Diamonds are gems formed deep in the earth over millions of years. Mining operations are carried out to acquire them. They are then cut, polished, and set into jewellery.</p><p>Mined Diamonds, also known as Natural Diamonds, are prized for their rarity and are quite expensive based on their size, cut, clarity, and color. You will find these commonly in many mainstream jewelry stores. You will also find Natural Diamonds in most vintage jewelry pieces. You can also find treated versions of Natural Diamonds, which are artificially enhanced for better clarity or colour.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bD88Lf": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "So… Which One Should You Choose?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>So… Which One Should You Choose?</h2><p>It really comes down to what matters most to you. Are you going for tradition? Sustainability? Something unique? A diamond’s value isn’t just about carats and clarity, it’s also about how it fits into your life.</p><p>Here are a few quick thoughts to guide you:</p><ul><li>If budget is a concern: Lab Grown Diamonds can offer great value.</li><li>If you want something different: Colored diamonds are wonderful ways to stand out.</li><li>If you care about impact: Lab Grown Diamonds are your best bet.</li></ul>",
            "custom_id": "choose"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_R7fJhY": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Conclusion</h2><p>All diamonds are not created the same. Knowing the differences gives you more control and a better shopping experience overall.</p><p>The right diamond isn't just about specs on a certificate. It’s about how it makes you feel when you wear it. Whether you go for a mined diamond or a modern lab grown marvel, make sure it’s a piece you’ll love every time it catches the light.</p><p>Because at the end of the day, it’s not just about owning a diamond. It’s about choosing the one that tells your story.</p>",
            "custom_id": "conclusion"
          }
        }
      },
